description.narrative: By 2021, UNICEF and its partners in WCAR are better equipped in leveraging more domestic resources for children right and in building sustainable social protection systems for resilience and early recovery., which contributes to Adolescent Empowerment, Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children, Social Protection. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2030, Every Child has Equitable Chance in Life.

title.narrative: By 2021, UNICEF and its partners in WCAR are better equipped in leveraging more domestic resources for children right and inbuilding sustainable social protection systems for resilience and early recovery.

description.narrative: In 2021, the resilience of children and families in WCAR remained challenged by multiple compounding shocks due to the continued socioeconomic impact of the COVID19 pandemic, the impact of climate change, and conflicts. Governments have not been able to recover economically given the increased needs for social sector spending, including social protection. Despite the improved macroeconomic outlook compared to 2020, government spending remains inadequate for social sectors due to low revenues, inefficiencies, and debt pressure. Financing constraints and capacity gaps also prevented sustainable scale up of social protection, despite temporary increases in coverage in response to the COVID-19 shock.;;; | Status:Met | As-of Date:28/01/2022
